records.addlTxt:
Defendant Andrew James Petrie in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered count dismissed and read-in.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 2 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions: 
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $240.00 to Josephina G.-R. or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Letter of apology to Josephina G.-R.;
*  No contact with Jsephina G.-R.;
*  Commit no new crimes;
*  Maintain full time employment;
*  Perform 25 hours of community service;
*  Pay all costs and surcharge or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

If the defendant pays restitution and completes the hours of community service within 6 months, the Court will grant expungement.
